```php
function paginateProducts($products, $page, $pageSize) {
    $offset = ($page - 1) * $pageSize;
    return array_slice($products, $offset, $pageSize);
}
```

You can use this function like so:

```php
$products = [
    ['id' => 1, 'name' => 'Product 1'],
    ['id' => 2, 'name' => 'Product 2'],
    // ...
];

$page = 1;
$pageSize = 10;

$pagedProducts = paginateProducts($products, $page, $pageSize);
```

This function takes an array of products and returns a new array that contains the specified number of products, starting from the offset calculated based on the page number.

Please note that this is a simple implementation. In a real-world application, you would likely want to add some error checking to ensure that the page and page size are valid (i.e., not less than 1 or greater than the total number of products).

